<subSubSection id="C30C49C9B00FD776A09D94A8FB0B719E" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" type="key">
<key id="FF874D73B00FD776A09D94A8FB0B719E" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<keyStep id="30E202E7B00FD776A09D94A8FB0A710A" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<paragraph id="8BA91A42B00FD776A09D94A8FB0B7143" blockId="1.[174,1233,716,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<keyLead id="30E7B977B00FD776A09D94A8FB0B7143" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
1. 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A0CA94A8FEC2709A" box="[249,281,716,737]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">orb</emphasis>
seta-like, numerous (10–40), arranded as a tuft in posterior part of parafrontalia (
<figureCitation id="132D06C7B00FD776A47E94A8FB4A709A" box="[1101,1169,716,738]" captionStart="Figs 20–21" captionStartId="18.[166,205,1098,1120]" captionTargetBox="[218,1177,182,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-310@18.[205,1193,174,1012]" captionText="Figs 20–21.Xerophilomyia nigropicta Rohd. 20 (male):a — habitus in lateral view; b — head in profile; c — head in frontal view; d — head in dorsal view; e — widdle leg in antrerior view; f — wing; g — abdomen in dorsal view; h — label. 21 (female): a —habitus in lateral view; b — abdomen in dorsal view; c — head in profile; d — head in frontal view; e — head in dorsal view; f — wing abdomen, lateral view; g — label." pageId="1" pageNumber="184">figs 20</figureCitation>
, b–d). Vibrissal angle placed above oral margin, lunula in lower part strongly narrowed (
<figureCitation id="132D06C7B00FD776A425948DFB8F7085" box="[1046,1108,745,767]" captionStart="Figs 20–21" captionStartId="18.[166,205,1098,1120]" captionTargetBox="[218,1177,182,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-310@18.[205,1193,174,1012]" captionText="Figs 20–21.Xerophilomyia nigropicta Rohd. 20 (male):a — habitus in lateral view; b — head in profile; c — head in frontal view; d — head in dorsal view; e — widdle leg in antrerior view; f — wing; g — abdomen in dorsal view; h — label. 21 (female): a —habitus in lateral view; b — abdomen in dorsal view; c — head in profile; d — head in frontal view; e — head in dorsal view; f — wing abdomen, lateral view; g — label." pageId="1" pageNumber="184">fig. 21</figureCitation>
, d). 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A44C9483FB557085" bold="true" box="[1151,1166,743,766]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">{</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A4A9948DFB7A7085" box="[1178,1185,745,766]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">t</emphasis>
<subScript id="17921807B00FD776A492949CFB73717F" attach="left" box="[1185,1192,760,772]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">2</subScript>
and often 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A1039561FEEC7161" box="[304,311,773,794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">f</emphasis>
2 with a ctenidium consisting of strong thick spine-like setae (
<figureCitation id="132D06C7B00FD776A3B09561FC1E7161" box="[899,965,773,795]" captionStart="Figs 20–21" captionStartId="18.[166,205,1098,1120]" captionTargetBox="[218,1177,182,1002]" captionTargetId="figure-310@18.[205,1193,174,1012]" captionText="Figs 20–21.Xerophilomyia nigropicta Rohd. 20 (male):a — habitus in lateral view; b — head in profile; c — head in frontal view; d — head in dorsal view; e — widdle leg in antrerior view; f — wing; g — abdomen in dorsal view; h — label. 21 (female): a —habitus in lateral view; b — abdomen in dorsal view; c — head in profile; d — head in frontal view; e — head in dorsal view; f — wing abdomen, lateral view; g — label." pageId="1" pageNumber="184">figs 20</figureCitation>
, e; 22, e)................................. ........................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1661C1B00FD776A3A39546FB0B7143" authority="Rohdendorf, 1925" authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1925" box="[912,1232,802,824]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Xerophilomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A3A39546FBC6714C" box="[912,1053,802,823]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Xerophilomyia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8767B3B00FD776A4119546FB0B7143" author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[1058,1232,802,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" pagination="61 - 72" refId="ref17051" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. 1925. Etudes sur les miltogrammines. II. Synopsis des apodacres palaeartiques. Encyclopedie Entomologique, B 2, 11 (1), 61 - 72." type="journal article" year="1925">Rohdendorf, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA91A42B00FD776A09D955BFB0A710A" blockId="1.[174,1233,716,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<keyLead id="30E7B977B00FD776A09D955BFB0A710A" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
— Proclinate 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A152955BFE5B712F" box="[353,384,831,852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">orb</emphasis>
absent or arranged as a row with 1–6 setae. Vibrissal angle placed at oral margin, lunula in lower part not narrowed. 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A234953EFDCD710A" bold="true" box="[519,534,858,881]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">{</emphasis>
: legs without ctenidium. ................................................................................2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E202E7B00FD776A09D951DFB0B719E" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<paragraph id="8BA91A42B00FD776A09D951DFB0B71D0" blockId="1.[174,1233,716,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<keyLead id="30E7B977B00FD776A09D951DFB0B71D0" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
2. Proclinate 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A153951DFEA471F5" box="[352,383,889,910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">orb</emphasis>
absent or present as 1–2 fine setae (figs 13, b–d). Postpedicel 4–10× as long as pedicel..... .................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1661C1B00FD776A3F195F2FB0B71D0" authority="Rohdendorf, 1925" authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1925" box="[962,1232,917,939]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Xeromyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A3F195F2FBC571D0" box="[962,1054,918,939]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Xeromyia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8767B3B00FD776A41095F1FB0B71D0" author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[1059,1232,917,939]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" pagination="61 - 72" refId="ref17051" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. 1925. Etudes sur les miltogrammines. II. Synopsis des apodacres palaeartiques. Encyclopedie Entomologique, B 2, 11 (1), 61 - 72." type="journal article" year="1925">Rohdendorf, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA91A42B00FD776A09D95D7FB0B719E" blockId="1.[174,1233,716,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<keyLead id="30E7B977B00FD776A09D95D7FB0B719E" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
— Proclinate 
<emphasis id="B962C650B00FD776A16C95D6FEA571BC" box="[351,382,946,967]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">orb</emphasis>
present as 3–6 pairs of strong setae (
<figureCitation id="132D06C7B00FD776A2E695D6FCE871BC" box="[725,819,946,968]" captionStart="Figs 1–2" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1728,1750]" captionTargetBox="[226,1199,722,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-322@2.[203,1209,718,1700]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–2. Apodacra chrysocephala Rohd.: 1 (male): a — habitus in lateral view; b — habitus in dorsal view; c — head in profile; d — head in frontal view; e — fore leg in anterior view; f — wing; g — label. 2(female): a — habitus in lateral view; b — abdomen in dorsal view; c — head in profile; d — head in frontal view; e — head in dorsal view; f — wing; g — label." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377614/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">figs 1, c; 2</figureCitation>
, c). Postpedicel 3–5× as long as pedicel (
<figureCitation id="132D06C7B00FD776A49E95D6FE99719E" captionStart="Figs 1–2" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1728,1750]" captionTargetBox="[226,1199,722,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-322@2.[203,1209,718,1700]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–2. Apodacra chrysocephala Rohd.: 1 (male): a — habitus in lateral view; b — habitus in dorsal view; c — head in profile; d — head in frontal view; e — fore leg in anterior view; f — wing; g — label. 2(female): a — habitus in lateral view; b — abdomen in dorsal view; c — head in profile; d — head in frontal view; e — head in dorsal view; f — wing; g — label." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377614/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">figs 1 d; 2 d</figureCitation>
). ...................................................................................................................... 
